    "title": "corp.funtap.vn视角： Funtap Games ｜早期指标分析",
    "page_range": "52",
    "summary": "This parent section provides a comprehensive analytical framework for evaluating early-stage player metrics, retention benchmarks, and scalability readiness for 4X strategy and classic SLG mobile games. It addresses the strategic necessity of early indicators, outlines specific analytical dimensions, and establishes stage-gate KPI thresholds required for successful global launches.\n\n**Topics & Entities:** Early metric validation, D1/D7 retention, first-week playtime behavior, session structure, global launch criteria, soft launch competitiveness, alliance onboarding, paid user acquisition (UA), and market creative trends. Key entities include Funtap Games, 4X strategy games, classic SLG, Android/iOS platforms, MOBA/RPG titles (comparative), whales, alliance/solo players, and the 广大大 (Advertiser Analysis Module).\n**Definitions:** FTUE (First Time User Experience), \"honeymoon period\" (initial engagement phase), \"high-frequency, low-duration\" session model (mindshare model), \"social watershed\" (retention divergence point), and the \"10-hour rule\" (600 cumulative minutes in week one increases paying user conversion probability by 5x).\n**Procedures & Strategies:** Implement a hybrid FTUE within the first 15 minutes of gameplay; mandate alliance/guild joining via main quests within 24 hours; heavily deploy speed-up items during Week 1 to eliminate wait times and establish a ~60-minute daily play habit before Week 2 economic tightening; trigger monetization prompts during D1/D2 playtime peaks; prevent early timer bloat to mitigate churn; and initiate paid UA testing early in the lifecycle to validate scalability.\n**Claims:** Early metrics are mandatory to verify player acceptance of operational hook strategies (e.g., mini-games). D7 retention depends almost entirely on social..."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0110",
    "title": "策略手游投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "55-56",
    "summary": "This section (pages 55–56) provides a data-driven analysis of 2025 advertising and user acquisition (UA) trends for strategy mobile games, leveraging analytics from the 广大大 (GuangdaDa) platform. It covers core genres including SLG, RTS, tower defense, building games, casual SLG, roguelike RPG, wuxia MMO, and mild-horror MMO across January–December 2025. The content outlines standardized ad creative procedures, specifically a narrative formula: high-altitude fall → number growth/choice gate parkour → smooth mid-level clearance → intentional failure. Key claims highlight that number gate parkour has emerged as the primary UA method for casual SLG, with traditional number-variable formats being replaced by three-lane tracks, new items, and moving choice gates. Traditional numerical/IP progression, idle, roguelike RPG, wuxia, and mild-horror MMO formats currently retain mainstream audio-visual promotional advantages. The section features two monthly trend figures (Jan–Dec 2025) detailing advertiser volume (4.0K–5.5K) and new creative launch ratios (77.2%–89.3%), alongside monthly average active creatives (0–400) and new creative ratios (53.0%–65.8%). Evidence is sourced from GuangdaDa’s Ad Creative and Advertiser Analysis modules, supported by statistical trend visualizations and comparative genre performance data. Optimized for retrieval on 2025 mobile game ad creative formulas, SLG/RTS UA strategy evolution, monthly advertiser/creative volume benchmarks, and genre-specific promotional metrics."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0112",
    "title": "RPG手游 投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "57-58",
    "summary": "This section examines advertising trends for RPG mobile games (RPG手游) from January to December 2025, utilizing analytics from the 广大大 (GuangdaDa) platform. **Topics** cover creative strategy evolution, advertiser activity, creative volume trends, and popular gameplay genres including Idle, Roguelike, MMO, Turn-based, Open World, Anime-style, and Manga/Comic Adaptation. **Entities** highlight emerging themes (Martial Arts, Supernatural Tales), specific creative tropes (AI character intros, unique item showcases, intentional failure, character customization, high-damage combos), and a high-performing subgenre (Realistic Management Simulation). **Procedures/Definitions** outline a standardized RPG ad creative sequence: AI character introduction → unique roguelike item showcase → multiple battles/map transitions → intentional failure → character customization → map/class display → high-damage combo clearance. **Claims** assert that exaggerated skill effects and rich art assets are primary ad features, niche themes are rising in popularity, realistic management mechanics show strong performance, and classic user-acquisition creatives exhibit a higher reuse rate in RPGs compared to other game genres. **Figures & Metrics** include Figure 1 (Monthly Advertiser Count Trend: 5.5K–7.5K advertisers, with 74.3%–87.0% launching new creatives monthly) and Figure 2 (Monthly Average Active Creatives Trend). **Evidence Types** consist of platform-derived monthly metric breakdowns, comparative genre performance data, and longitudinal trend analysis across the 2025 calendar year."
  },
