    "title": "模拟手游 投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "59-60",
    "summary": "This section supports retrieval for queries on advertising placement trends and creative strategies in simulation mobile games, covering the full year from January to December 2025. It addresses key topics and entities including simulation management, realistic simulators, sandbox, makeup/dress-up, interactive fiction, hybrid casual games, and mini-game collection platforms. Documented ad creative procedures detail two standard 2025 narrative patterns: (1) interactive choice → plot development → intentional failure → tragic ending, and (2) affair/cuckold plot → problem solving → option tug-of-war → intentional failure. Key claims indicate that mini-game side modes function as effective user-acquisition tools, niche themes drive higher player attention, top hybrid casual titles dominate downloads and revenue, mini-game collection platforms are rapidly gaining market share, and fast trend-following iteration is critical for casual game breakout success. Metrics and figures track monthly average active ad creative volume and the percentage of new creatives launched throughout 2025, with specific monthly new creative rates provided (Jan 44.8%, Feb 44.1%, Mar 47.2%, Apr 48.8%, May 41.7%, Jun 47.9%, Jul 51.3%, Aug 48.5%, Sep 49.1%, Oct 46.5%, Nov 46.9%, Dec 49.7%). Evidence is sourced from GuangdaDa’s Ad Creative Module and Advertiser Analysis Module, utilizing industry analytics, monthly performance metrics, trend charts, and observational market claims."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0116",
    "title": "休闲手游 投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "61-62",
    "summary": "This section (pages 61–62) analyzes casual mobile game advertising trends and creative strategies across January–December 2025. It outlines standard creative procedures, specifically the \"AI opening → actual gameplay → gameplay showcase\" and \"viral video opening → in-game recreation → gameplay showcase\" workflows. Key entities covered include casual mobile games, popular mechanics (parkour, jumping, matching, water sorting), top puzzle genres (Mahjong connect, Sudoku, word puzzles, solitaire), and data platforms GuangdaDa and TikTok. Core claims assert that entertaining content has become the baseline for ad openings, future creatives will increasingly source directly from TikTok trends or creator videos, and video formats significantly outperform others in impression share for leading puzzle games. Performance metrics are visualized in two monthly trend figures tracking advertiser volume (~7.0K–10.0K), new creative launch rates (~76.9%–86.8%), average active creatives (0–300), and new creative percentages (~43.4%–53.5%). Evidence is drawn from GuangdaDa’s Ad Creative and Advertiser Analysis modules, utilizing platform analytics, trend forecasting, and impression share benchmarking."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0119",
    "title": "益智解谜手游 投放趋势观察",
    "page_range": "63-64",
    "summary": "This retrieval-optimized summary covers the parent section \"益智解谜手游 投放趋势观察\" (Puzzle Mobile Game Advertising Trend Observation, pp. 63–64) and its associated child content. It is structured to support queries on:\n- **Topics & Entities:** Puzzle/brain-teaser mobile game advertising, core gameplay mechanics (mahjong elimination, Sudoku, coloring, brain-teasers, line-connecting), and analytics sourced from the 广大大 (Guangda Da) ad creative and advertiser analysis modules.\n- **Dates:** January 2025 through December 2025.\n- **Procedures & Creative Formulas:** Standard ad material sequence (micro-horror/eerie BGM → unique prop display → intentional failure → real-world prop recreation → gameplay demonstration → download prompt) and an emerging trend favoring direct in-game level footage paired with short-video prank hooks.\n- **Tables, Figures & Metrics:** Two 2025 monthly trend visualizations tracking: (1) advertiser counts and the percentage deploying new materials (~83.1%–89.2%, scale: 0–40K); (2) monthly average active ad materials and the percentage of new materials (~65.9%–76.1%, scale: 0–150).\n- **Claims & Evidence Types:** Claims that entertainment/casino mobile games lead all categories in YoY growth and image ad share, with gold, USD, and cash notes identified as the highest-attention visual elements. Evidence is derived from platform analytics, monthly deployment data, and heat/popularity rankings.\n- **Retrieval Utility:** Optimized for questions regarding 2025 mobile game ad routines, creative trend forecasts, monthly advertiser/material activity rates, and high-performing visual hooks in gaming campaigns."
  },
