    "title": "媒体声音",
    "page_range": "67-68",
    "summary": "**Topics:** Chinese mobile game and enterprise overseas expansion trends (2023–2026), genre-specific growth drivers (SLG, Merge/Hybrid casual), market consolidation vs. innovation, domestic vs. overseas mini-game dynamics, and PC/console (Steam) market developments.\n**Entities:** Publishers/Platforms (Tencent, TikTok, Moonton, Chinese publishers, Turkish studios); Games/Titles (*Whiteout Survival*, *Kingshot*, *Last Z*, *Land of Prison*, *Gossip Harbor*, 《抓大鹅》, 《永远的蔚蓝海岸》, 《生存33天》, 《三角洲行动》, 《少女前线 2》, 《无尽对决》, 《黑神话：悟空》, 《明末：渊墟之羽》, 《饿殍：明末千里行》, 《峰火十四》); Markets/Regions (US, Japan, South Korea, Europe, China).\n**Dates/Timeframes:** Late 2020 (start of product model exploration), 2023 (market testing/adjustment phase), 2024 (major title releases), 2025 (current review period, \"quality leap\" phase, strategic pivot), 2026 (projected industry focus), and a six-year consecutive milestone (overseas revenue >100B RMB).\n**Definitions/Concepts:** SLG, Merge/Synthesis casual, Hybrid casual, LTV, secondary vs. main gameplay integration, short-drama narrative mechanics, \"Adjustment\" phase (contrasting 2023 product-model testing with 2025 traffic-driven retreat), \"Traffic-driven打法\" (user acquisition/ad-buying focus), \"Numerical-value导向模型\" (stat/progression-driven design paired with ad spending).\n**Procedures/Strategies:** Adapting PC/Steam premium mechanics for mobile; scaling live-ops event frequency; integrating high-intensity, plot-twist narratives; benchmarking Turkish hybrid casual models; pivoting from experimental product models to established traffic-acquisition strategies; cross-regional promotion of legacy titles; platform revenue-sharing policy adjustments; leveraging gameplay fusion and cultural empowerment.\n**Claims:** SLG is the largest game subcategory in 2025; Merge games..."
